&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%AE" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 class="relative group">Gurvashtaka
&lt;div id="gurvashtaka" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#gurvashtaka" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;audio controls>
&lt;source src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dasarpai/DAI-mp3/main/dasarpai-mp3/013-GuruvAshtakam.mp3" type="audio/mp3">
Your browser does not support the audio element.
&lt;/audio>
&lt;p>शरीरं सुरुपं तथा वा कलत्रं यशश्चारू चित्रं धनं मेरुतुल्यम् । &lt;br>
मनश्चेन्न लग्नं गुरोरंघ्रिपद्मे ततः किं ततः किं ततः किं ततः किम् ।।१।।&lt;/p>
&lt;p>कलत्रं धनं पुत्रपौत्रादि सर्वं गृहं बान्धवाः सर्वमेतद्धि जातम् । &lt;br>
मनश्चेन्न लग्नं गुरोरंघ्रिपद्मे ततः किं ततः किं ततः किं ततः किम् ।।२।।&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Relevance Of Guru</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/relevance-of-guru/</link><pubDate>Mon, 30 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/relevance-of-guru/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5115-Relevance-Of-Guru.jpg" alt="Relevance Of Guru" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Relevance Of Guru
&lt;div id="relevance-of-guru" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#relevance-of-guru" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Without Questions in life what is the need for a Guru? &lt;br>
If my questions are well defined then do I need a Guru? &lt;br>
Guru helps in defining questions well &lt;br>
or answering whatever you ask? &lt;br>
Does he empower you by giving more information &lt;br>
or make you restless by holding half answer?&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Who Is Guru</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/who-is-guru/</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Aug 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/who-is-guru/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5029-Who-Is-Guru.jpg" alt="Who Is Guru" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Who Is Guru
&lt;div id="who-is-guru" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#who-is-guru" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>We all know the Samskrut definition of Guru &lt;br>
The remover of darkness. &lt;br>
But whose darkness? &lt;br>
How does he remove? &lt;br>
What is this darkness about? &lt;br>
What is the meaning of remove?&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In Omkara Dharma tradition, &lt;br>
Knowledge &amp;amp; Wisdom has been so important &lt;br>
that from the time immemorial &lt;br>
Many people came forward. &lt;br>
At the time of leaving for the cause of Knowledge &amp;amp; Wisdom &lt;br>
Some of these people had comfortable life and some didn’t&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>